Hello everyone,
I am trying to set httpheader parameters but somehow it is not getting set. I have tried all the possible ways but cant seem to point out the issue. This is happening only in one component bcoz when I tested the same code in a different component the values set properly inside the header.

Currently I am using Angular 7.0.4 
This is a small part of the code where I am assigning the header:
const httpOptions = {
      headers: new HttpHeaders({
        'Access-Control-Allow-Origin': httpHeaderData.get('Access-Control-Allow-Origin'),
        'Content-Type': httpHeaderData.get('Content-Type'),
        'token': httpHeaderData.get('token'),
      }),
      headerData: new HttpParams().set('token', httpHeaderData.get('token')),
      withCredentials: true
    };
    const headers = new HttpHeaders({
      'Access-Control-Allow-Origin': httpHeaderData.get('Access-Control-Allow-Origin'),
      'Content-Type': httpHeaderData.get('Content-Type'),
      'token': httpHeaderData.get('token'),
    });
    headers.set('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', httpHeaderData.get('Access-Control-Allow-Origin'));

